composeJaxWsTargetNamespaceByPackage

public static java.lang.String composeJaxWsTargetNamespaceByPackage(java.lang.String packageName)
An utility method for composing a default target namespace for JaxWs customization out of a package name. Algorithm:
  • In case the package has 0 fragment (default package) the result would be http:///
  • In case the package has 1 fragment the result would be http://fragment1/
  • In case the package has 2 fragments the result would be http://fragment2.fragment1/
  • In case the package has more than 2 fragments the result would be http://fragment2.fragment1/fragment3/fragment4/.../fragmentn/

    • Parameters:
    packageName - Name of the package
    Returns:
    the composed namespace

    getServiceName

    public static java.lang.String getServiceName(org.eclipse.jdt.core.IType endpointType)
    Removes the "Bean" suffix from the endpointType in case it is present and generates Service name for the specified IType.

    Parameters:
    endpoint - class.
    Returns:
    Service name for the @WebService annotation, the name of the endpointType without the "Bean" suffix and "Service" at the end. In case the name of the endpointType equals "Bean" then the original name is returned with "Service" ate the end.
    Throws:
    java.lang.NullPointerException - when endpointType specified is null
